The Weather Service said normal temperatures are expected for the Atlantic states from Virginia south, and for the Gulf Coast states. Normal precipitation is forecast for the Atlantic and Gulf coast states, along with the Northwest and northern Mountain States. On Tuesday the Agriculture Department reported sharp declines in the outlook for several crops. The disappointing forecast came as President Reagan headed to the Midwest to inspect drought-plagued farms. A new climate assessment of the ongoing drought said many areas now experiencing extreme drought have less than a 4 percent chance of recovering from the drought within 3 months. 